---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
---

<DocsLayout title="Juca" description="Frontend hub for lawyers in the sens.legal ecosystem.">
  <h1>Juca</h1>
  <p class="subtitle">Frontend hub for lawyers</p>

  <span class="badge badge-dev">dev</span>

  <p>
    Juca is the interface through which legal professionals interact with the
    sens.legal ecosystem. It organizes briefing, reading, canvas, and workflow
    experiences for Brazilian lawyers, acting as the frontend hub of the product.
  </p>

  <p>
    The legal backend is moving out of Juca and into Valter. That means search,
    graph logic, reasoning, verification, and legal pipelines stop being owned
    by the frontend and become canonical backend services consumed by it.
  </p>

  <h2>Responsibilities</h2>

  <ul>
    <li>Orchestrate briefing and argument-building experiences for end users</li>
    <li>Consume Valter as the backend for jurisprudence, reasoning, and verification</li>
    <li>Consume Leci for legislative grounding as the integration matures</li>
    <li>Keep the focus on UX, interface state, and user workflows</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Stack</h2>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Framework:</strong> Next.js 15</li>
    <li><strong>Language:</strong> TypeScript</li>
    <li><strong>UI:</strong> React, Tailwind CSS</li>
    <li><strong>Deploy:</strong> Vercel</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Current status</h2>

  <ul>
    <li>Briefing, canvas, and reading flows remain the center of the product</li>
    <li>Recent PR work has focused on frontend stability and pipeline unblocking</li>
    <li>The backend migration into Valter remains the canonical direction</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Links</h2>

  <ul>
    <li><a href="https://juca.sens.legal" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Documentation</a></li>
    <li><a href="https://github.com/sensdiego/juca" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub</a></li>
  </ul>
</DocsLayout>

